{{Infobox scientist |name = Brian Weiss |image = BLWEISS.jpg |image_size = |caption = Brian Weiss in 2012 |birth_name = Brian Leslie Weiss |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1944|11|06}} |birth_place = [[New York City]], USA |death_date = |death_place = |residence = [[Miami]], [[Florida]] |citizenship = [[United States|American]] |nationality = [[United States]] |field = [[Psychiatry]] |work_institutions = |alma_mater = [[Columbia University]], [[Yale University]] |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = Reincarnation research |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = |website = {{URL|http://www.brianweiss.com/}} }}
'''Brian Leslie Weiss''' (born November 6, 1944) is an American [[psychiatrist]], [[hypnotherapist]], and author who specializes in so-called ''[[past life regression]]'', a field identified as [[pseudoscience]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://sciencebasedmedicine.org/past-life-regression-therapy-encouraging-fantasy/ |title=Past Life Regression Therapy: Encouraging Fantasy |date=2016-07-26 |website=Science-Based Medicine |language=en-US |access-date=2018-07-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Bodkin |first=J. A. |date=2003-07-09 |title=Science and Pseudoscience in Clinical Psychology |url=https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/article-abstract/196867 |journal=JAMA: The Journal of the American Medical Association |language=en |volume=290 |issue=2 |pages=268–269 |doi=10.1001/jama.290.2.268 |issn=0098-7484}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=c6PACQAAQBAJ&pg=PA127&lpg=PA127&dq=%2522past+life+regression%2522+pseudoscience&source=bl&ots=7uaTHSXS10&sig=9xrLBdwxNVpuGyRHrJbXyl8xqzI&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi6lcLGyovcAhUJDcAKHQ_wCe04ChDoAQhMMAg#v=onepage&q=%2522past%2520life%2520regression%2522%2520pseudoscience&f=false |title=Pseudoscience: A Critical Encyclopedia: A Critical Encyclopedia |last=Regal |first=Brian |date=2009-10-15 |publisher=ABC-CLIO |isbn=9780313355080 |language=en}}</ref> His research includes purported [[reincarnation]], [[past life regression]], future life progression, and survival of the human [[Soul (spirit)|soul]] after death.
==Education and medical career== Weiss studied at [[Columbia University]],<ref name=nyt10/> and later graduated from the Yale University School of Medicine in 1970, completing an internship in [[internal medicine]] at the [[New York University Medical Center]] then returning to Yale for a two-year [[Residency (medicine)|residency]] in psychiatry.<ref>http://ww2.doh.state.fl.us/irm00Profiling/ProfileEDUC.asp?LicId=16269&ProfNBR=1501</ref> He went on to become Head of Psychiatry, [[Mount Sinai Medical Center & Miami Heart Institute|Mount Sinai Medical Center]], Miami.<ref>{{cite news |title=Past Lives |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=O8IzAAAAIBAJ&sjid=kDIHAAAAIBAJ&pg=7105,7614788&dq=mount+sinai+dr+brian+weiss&hl=en |publisher=Lodi News-Sentinel |date=Oct 19, 1989 |accessdate=June 3, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title= Doctor Details Patient's Past Lives|url= |publisher=Miami Herald |date= May 29, 1989|page=6B |accessdate=}}</ref>
==Past life regression and future life progression== According to Weiss, in 1980 one of his patients, "Catherine", began discussing past-life experiences under [[hypnosis]]. Weiss did not believe in reincarnation at the time but, after confirming elements of Catherine's stories through public records, came to be convinced of the survival of an element of the human personality after death.<ref name=rl1xxx>[http://www.post-gazette.com/seen/breakfast/20020805break0805p1.asp Breakfast with Brian Weiss], ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette'', August 5, 2002, Accessed April 25, 2009.</ref> Weiss claims he has regressed more than 4,000 patients since 1980.<ref>Weinstein-Moser, Edie. [http://wisdom-magazine.com/Article.aspx/478/ "Interview with Brian Weiss"]. ''Wisdom'' magazine. ''Wisdom-Magazine.com''. 2008. Retrieved June 18, 2015.</ref>
Weiss advocates [[hypnotic regression]] as therapy, claiming that many phobias and ailments are rooted in past-life experiences whose acknowledgment by the patient can have a curative effect. Weiss also writes about [[Mediumship|messages]] received from the "Masters", or "super-evolved, nonphysical souls", he claims to have communicated with through his subjects.<ref>http://www.brianweiss.com/about-the-books/messages-from-the-masters/</ref> Weiss holds workshops and seminars across the United States that explain and teach self-regression mediations techniques. This includes the Hay House I Can Do It one day workshops and the intense experiential workshops at the Omega Institute for Holistic Studies in NY.
==Personal life== Weiss lives with his wife Carole in [[Miami]], Florida, where he writes and conducts public seminars and workshops on the subject of reincarnation.<ref name=nyt10>{{cite web|last=Miller|first=Lisa|title=Remembrances of Lives Past|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/29/fashion/29PastLives.html?pagewanted=all&_r=1&|publisher=The New York Times|date=August 27, 2010}}</ref> His daughter Amy E. Weiss is the co-author of his 2012 book ''Miracles Happen: The Transformational Healing Power of Past-Life Memories''.<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/0062201220 ''Miracles Happen: The Transformational Healing Power of Past-Life Memories'']</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Woman relives the spooky experience with past-life regression |publisher=Daily Mail| url = http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2336088/Immediately-I-saw-body-old-man-long-white-hair-living-Middle-Ages-Woman-relives-spooky-experience-past-life-regression.html|date= 5 June 2013 | accessdate = 2014-06-25 }}</ref>
==Bibliography== * ''Many Lives, Many Masters: The True Story of a Prominent Psychiatrist, His Young Patient, and the Past-Life Therapy That Changed Both Their Lives'' (1988). {{ISBN|0-671-65786-0}} * ''Through Time into Healing: Discovering the Power of Regression Therapy to Erase Trauma and Transform Mind, Body and Relationships '' (1993). {{ISBN|0-7499-1835-7}}. * ''Only Love Is Real: A Story of Soulmates Reunited'' (1997) {{ISBN|0-7499-1620-6}}. * ''Messages From the Masters: Tapping into the Power of Love'' (2001). {{ISBN|0-7499-2167-6}} * ''Mirrors of Time: Using Regression for Physical, Emotional, and Spiritual Healing'' (2002). {{ISBN|1-5617-0929-8}}. * ''Same Soul, Many Bodies: Discover the Healing Power of Future Lives through Progression Therapy'' (2005). {{ISBN|0-7499-2541-8}}. {{ISBN|0-7432-6434-7}}. * ''Miracles Happen: The Transformational Healing Power of Past Life Memories'' (2012) {{ISBN|978-0-06-220122-5}}
