{{primary sources|date=July 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{use Indian English|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox university |name = Central Institute of Medicinal and Aromatic Plants |image_name = |established = 1959 |type = Research institution |director = Prof. [[Anil Kumar Tripathi]] |city = [[Lucknow]] |state = [[Uttar Pradesh]] |country = [[India]] |campus = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |website = [https://web.archive.org/web/20120415173956/http://www.cimap.res.in/cimapdev/index.php www.cimap.res.in] }}
'''Central Institute of Medicinal and Aromatic Plants''' (CIMAP) is a research institute of Council of Scientific and Industrial Research (CSIR) with its headquarter in Lucknow. It is engaged in the field of science and business of [[Herbalism|medicinal]] and [[Aromaticity|aromatic]] plants. CIMAP has four research centers situated in Bangalore, Hyderabad, Pantnagar and Purara (near Bageshwar, Uttarakhand).
