'''Fibromuscular Dysplasia Society of America''' is an American health charity that deals with [[fibromuscular dysplasia]], a [[vascular disease]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.crainscleveland.com/article/20090223/FREE/302239977/1007&template=printart |title=Nurse's rare disease work earns her national attention |last=Mortland |first= Shannon |date= February 23, 2009 |work=Crain's Cleveland Business |accessdate=October 8, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB124709683951414973?mod=googlewsj |title=Letters: 'Rare' Disease Raises Issues of Probability, Diagnosis |date=July 9, 2009 |work=The Wall Street Journal |accessdate=October 8, 2013}}</ref>
The society sponsors a registry of patients with fibromuscular dysplasia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cathlabdigest.com/Fibromuscular-Dysplasia-Registry-Results-0|title=Fibromuscular Dysplasia: The Registry and Results|work=Cath Lab Digest|accessdate=October 8, 2013}}</ref>
