{{Infobox lake | name = Tisleifjorden | image = Tisleifjorden_001.jpg | caption = Tisleifjorden from Auenhaugen | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Oppland]], [[Buskerud]] | coords = {{Coord|60|51|33|N|08|56|16|E|type:waterbody_region:NO|display=inline,title}} | type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = Norway | length = | width = | area = {{convert|13.54|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = {{convert|819|m|ft|abbr=on}} | islands = | cities = }} [[File:Tisleifjorden_dam.jpg|thumb|250px|Tisleifjorden dam]] '''Tisleifjorden''' is a Norwegian [[lake]] which lies in [[Nord-Aurdal]] municipality in [[Oppland]] county, as well in [[Gol, Norway|Gol]] and [[Hemsedal]] municipalities in [[Buskerud]] county. Tisleifjorden is dammed for [[hydroelectric]] power. The height of the lake can vary up to 11 meters. It is {{convert|13.54|km2|abbr=on}} in area and 32.53&nbsp;km around. It has an elevation of 819&nbsp;m above sea level. Tisleifjorden Dam creates a reservoir for the Åbjøra kraftverk hydro-electric power plant at Aurdalsfjord in Oppland. The power plant was built in the years 1949-1951 and was rebuilt in 2002. Åbjøra kraftverk is operated by [[Skagerak Energi]]. <ref>[https://snl.no/Tisleifjorden ''Tisleifjorden'' (Store norske leksikon. Geir Thorsnæs)]</ref> <ref>[https://snl.no/%C3%85bj%C3%B8ra_kraftverk ''Åbjøra kraftverk'' (Store norske leksikon. Knut A Rosvold)]</ref> <ref>[http://www.statkraft.no/Energikilder/vaare-kraftverk/norge/Abjora/ ''Åbjøra'' (Statkraft)]</ref>
